node.text:
Republicans think if they can win in California, they can push policies everywhere to attack women's rights, reproductive rights, voting rights, and workers’ rights.⁣
⁣
We will show them they’re not going to get this done. Not here. Never.

node.text:
California, voting is underway! Let’s keep @GavinNewsom fighting for Californians in Sacramento and keep the state and nation moving forward.

Vote NO on the recall. Sign your envelope and return your mail-in ballot or vote in person by September 14.

node.text: This Labor Day, remember to support and thank our union members. It’s because of unions and the determination of workers across the country that we have better wages, safer working conditions, and sick days. When unions are strong, America is strong.

A blue graphic with a screenshot of a Kamala Harris tweet that reads: Texas law SB8 blatantly violates the constitutional right established under Roe v. Wade nearly five decades ago.

It will disproportionately affect communities of color and individuals with low incomes from getting access to the health care they need.

We must protect that right.

node.text: Texas law SB8 will significantly impair people’s access to the health care they need, particularly for communities of color and individuals with low incomes. We are committed to protecting the right established by Roe v. Wade.
